    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon</strong> <strong>lardons</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the lardons are crisp, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>butter </strong>to the pot</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek </strong>with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[675ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, reduce the heat to medium, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>chicken stock </strong>to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until the carrot and potato are fork-tender, stirring occasionally</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the carrot and potato are fork-tender, stir through your <strong>soft</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>bacon, leek & potato chowder</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-leek-and-sweet-potato-chowder/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bacon, leek & potato chowder</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
